<p>On the basis of the desirability function [
 <xref rid="pone.0244749.ref025" ref-type="bibr">25</xref>], the extraction yields of polysaccharides and triterpenoids were compiled into one index (
 <italic>D</italic> value) according to Eqs (
 <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="pone.0244749.e002">2</xref>) and (
 <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="pone.0244749.e003">3</xref>): 
 <disp-formula id="pone.0244749.e002">
  <alternatives>
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0244749.e002.jpg" id="pone.0244749.e002g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M2">
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>d</mi>
      <mi>i</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mrow>
      <mo>{</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mtable>
        <mtr>
         <mtd>
          <mn>0</mn>
         </mtd>
        </mtr>
        <mtr>
         <mtd>
          <mrow>
           <mstyle scriptlevel="+1">
            <mfrac>
             <mrow>
              <msub>
               <mi>Y</mi>
               <mi>i</mi>
              </msub>
              <mo>−</mo>
              <msub>
               <mi>Y</mi>
               <mrow>
                <mi mathvariant="normal">min</mi>
               </mrow>
              </msub>
             </mrow>
             <mrow>
              <msub>
               <mi>Y</mi>
               <mrow>
                <mi mathvariant="normal">max</mi>
               </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>−</mo>
              <msub>
               <mi>Y</mi>
               <mrow>
                <mi mathvariant="normal">min</mi>
               </mrow>
              </msub>
             </mrow>
            </mfrac>
           </mstyle>
          </mrow>
         </mtd>
        </mtr>
        <mtr>
         <mtd>
          <mn>1</mn>
         </mtd>
        </mtr>
       </mtable>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
     <mspace width="1em"/>
     <mtable>
      <mtr>
       <mtd>
        <mrow>
         <msub>
          <mi>Y</mi>
          <mi>i</mi>
         </msub>
         <mo>≤</mo>
         <msub>
          <mi>Y</mi>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="normal">min</mi>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
        </mrow>
       </mtd>
      </mtr>
      <mtr>
       <mtd>
        <mrow>
         <msub>
          <mi>Y</mi>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="normal">min</mi>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mo>&lt;</mo>
         <msub>
          <mi>Y</mi>
          <mi>i</mi>
         </msub>
         <mo>&lt;</mo>
         <msub>
          <mi>Y</mi>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="normal">max</mi>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
        </mrow>
       </mtd>
      </mtr>
      <mtr>
       <mtd>
        <mrow>
         <msub>
          <mi>Y</mi>
          <mi>i</mi>
         </msub>
         <mo>≥</mo>
         <msub>
          <mi>Y</mi>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="normal">max</mi>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
        </mrow>
       </mtd>
      </mtr>
     </mtable>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
  <label>(2)</label>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic>Y</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>i</italic>
 </sub> is the response value of an 
 <italic>i</italic>-analyzed factor. 
 <disp-formula id="pone.0244749.e003">
  <alternatives>
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0244749.e003.jpg" id="pone.0244749.e003g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M3">
    <mrow>
     <mi>D</mi>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <msubsup>
      <mi>d</mi>
      <mn>1</mn>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mi>w</mi>
        <mn>1</mn>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </msubsup>
     <mo>×</mo>
     <msubsup>
      <mi>d</mi>
      <mn>2</mn>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mi>w</mi>
        <mn>2</mn>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </msubsup>
     <mo>×</mo>
     <mo>…</mo>
     <mo>×</mo>
     <msubsup>
      <mi>d</mi>
      <mi>m</mi>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mi>w</mi>
        <mi>m</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </msubsup>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
  <label>(3)</label>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic>d</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>i</italic>
 </sub> represents individual desirability value and 
 <italic>w</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>i</italic>
 </sub> is relative importance, which indicates the difference in the importance ascribed to different response variables. In Eq (
 <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="pone.0244749.e003">3</xref>), 
 <italic>w</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>i</italic>
 </sub> should be in the range of 0−1, and 
 <italic>w</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>1</italic>
 </sub> + 
 <italic>w</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>2</italic>
 </sub> + … + 
 <italic>w</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>3</italic>
 </sub> is 1.
</p>
